# Local Package Independence

Local packages must not depend on other local packages, with the following exceptions.

## Allowed Dependencies

1. **DependencyContainer** may depend on any local package.
2. **View packages** (created from `templates/Package.view.swift`) may depend on **DesignSystem**.
3. **View packages** may depend on other **view packages**.

All other cross-package dependencies are prohibited. Logic packages (created from `templates/Package.logic.swift`) must remain fully independent of every other local package.

## Decoupling

When a capability must cross package boundaries without adding an allowed `Package.swift` dependency, define the abstraction (for example a protocol shaped for the consumer’s needs) in the **consuming module**, keep concrete types in the **provider module**, and connect them in **DependencyContainer** or the **Biker** app.

For the step-by-step workflow, read and follow [.cursor/skills/local-package-decoupling/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/local-package-decoupling/SKILL.md).
